"I don't want to be wrong, but I have the feeling that we are somewhere passing a point beyond which movement will no longer be a reversal, it will be a movement forward," he added.
Kosachev called another "interesting and important feeling" in this context "a request for a Russian vision of how the modern world should develop."
"I attended many meetings of the head of the Russian delegation [at the session of the General Assembly] of the Minister of Foreign Affairs Sergei Lavrov, and I held my own meetings, and I saw with great pleasure that if another year or two or five years ago, the Russian opinion, the Russian vision of what is happening in the world, by and large, no one was interested, then now the situation is different," stated the chairman of the committee of the Council of Federation.
According to him, this is due to the fact that "the so-called new liberal order, which is personified with the West, has no answers to questions about how to solve world problems due to an obvious shortage of ideas in the global space, a shortage of ideas on how to solve the problems of the Middle East, the problems of terrorism, the problems of non-proliferation of nuclear weapons, the problems of migration."
