RF Ministry of Finance forecasts the ruble exchange rate for 17 years ahead
The Ministry of Finance of Russia expects a gradual weakening of the exchange rate of the rouble - up to 73.9 roubles per dollar by 2031-2035, follows from the draft long-term budget forecast submitted to the State Duma together with the draft federal budget.
In 2021-2025, the exchange rate of the rouble, according to forecast, will amount to 66.4 roubles per dollar, in 2026-2030 - 71.1 roubles, and in the next five years - 73.9.
The agency notes that these figures are a nominal rate.
The real effective rate (a measure that takes into account the exchange rates of the countries that are the main trading partners of the Russian Federation) will remain stable, officials assure.
As far as inflation is concerned, it will amount to 3.5% by 2020, and will then stabilize at around 4%, the Ministry of Finance believes.
